Singer Chibuzor Oji aka Faze has been is bereaved following the demise of his mother. The singer, who was a member of the defunct hip hop group, Plantashun Boyz, announced this on his Instagram page. He said his mother died on January 12, 2022, a year after he lost his twin sister. The 45-year-old “Originality” singer wondered why people he loves seem to be leaving him.   Ex-BBNaija’s Nina blasts Nigerians in Diaspora…     Six celebrities who became parents by surrogacy     Nigerian-American rapper, King Joel rewards school with…   He, however, consoled himself that God is omniscient and his mother is in a place void of troubles. - Advertisement - Sharing a photo of his late mum, Faze wrote: “I don’t know how to express what’s in my heart. My heart is heavy. My Mum passed on last Wednesday, January 12th. “This, after my twin sister left this world last year. I don’t know why so many good people I love are leaving but I just hold on to the thought that God is God and he knows what he is doing. “It is well. I just thank Him that she lived a full life and is done with the troubles of this world. Rest well Mummy.”